a. Draw a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to reflect the unrecorded loan releases of ₱2,852,351.33 for the Subaan River Protection Dike and ₱8,231,188.41 for the Solid Waste Management Facility with Equipment;

b. Reverse the entries made for the adjustment of ₱2,408.15 and ₱337,977.86 to cover the negative balance of the account, set up of loan releases totaling ₱3,842,475.29, adjustment of ₱3,374,376.95 for the understatement of loan in 2011, and set-up loans payable amounting to ₱2,200,000.00;

c. Effect the adjustment of interest expense erroneously debited in Loan Payable-Domestic account totaling ₱9,809,916.72;

d. obtain with the MDFO the loan balances as of         year-end for the projects SRP Dike and SWMF as guide to establish the correct balance of unpaid loans; and



e. maintain separate subsidiary ledgers for loans payable and interest payments for every loan obtained to facilitate monitoring and detection of unrecorded loan releases, principal and interest payments.

For future related transactions, recognize the liability based on actual releases, and refrain from deducting interest payments on the principal balance of loan, rather record the payment under Interest Expense account.

