We recommended  and Management agreed that the Honorable Mayor direct all offices and accountable personnel concerned to report all unserviceable properties for purposes of;

(i) dropping the same from the inventory report of PPE, and

(ii) record those properties to the IIRUP. Further, the Municipal Inventory Team conduct complete inventory of all unserviceable properties and prepare and the required IIRUP so that disposal could be effected pursuant to applicable laws, rules and regulations on the supply and property management.

We recommended and Management agreed that the MDRRM Officer and other concerned LGU Officials to:

a. attend trainings relative the ICS and establish the ICS in accordance with Rule 7 (h), Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) of Republic Act (RA) 10121 and NDRRMC Memorandum Circular No. 4, s. 2012, dated March 28, 2012;

b. Update the Contingency Plans to include minimum information on the activation of early warning system, center management, and other scheme as required under IRR Rule 6, Section 4(3) of RA 10121;

c. Attend trainings on CBDRRM and immediately conduct the same seminar on barangays of the Municipality; and


d. Prioritize and implement the programs, projects and activities identified during the year to ensure the readiness of the Municipality in case of disaster; and provide adequate safeguard and storage for all response and emergency equipment, and budget for the installation of signages and markers in identified and danger zones.
